----------------------------------
BOM: Browser Object Model
- allows JS to interact with the web browser


Window is the core of the object model

-------------
SYSTEM DIALOGS

alert(), confirm(), prompt() -- are made available because of the window object;

----------------
setInterval() and setTimeout()

setInterval() allows code to be executed at a specified time interval and will continue until
clearInterval() is called

setTimeout() allows code to be executed after a specified time has passed and will only be passed once
and can be cancelled after clearTimeout() is called

